title: Subramanian Doraiswamy slams second Kanga League ton on the trot
text:
Subramanian Doraiswamy slams second Kanga League ton on the trot By A Correspondent | Posted 1 hour 
DY Patil Sports Academy's (DYPSA) Subramanian Doraiswamy scored his second Kanga League 'A' division century on the trot yesterday against former champions National Cricket Club at Navi Mumbai. DY Patil Sports Academy's Subramanian Doraiswamy 
His October 2 effort against Parsee Gymkhana helped his team win, but yesterday, the match ended in a draw. Yogesh Pawar (51), Shoaib Shaikh (31) were the other main scorers while National's Rohan Raje claimed 2 for 72. 
DYPSA declared at 255 for 5 to which National CC ended up scoring 94 for three with Ashay Sardesai top-scoring with an unbeaten 42. 
Payyade SC win In another premier division encounter, Payyade Sports Club clinched a first innings victory over Muslim United SC. Payyade scored 212 for 7 declared thanks to Musavir Khote (61), Bravish Shetty (56) even as Salil Agharkar claimed 4 for 71. Muslim United were bowled out for 86 with pacer Usman Malvi claiming 4-32 and leggie Pardeep Sahu 3-4. Tags:
